to be on your email list.

505
00:21:26,080 --> 00:21:29,290
So yes, you can just download
the emails from your Etsy

506
00:21:29,290 --> 00:21:32,260
customers, but you can't really
get away with adding them

507
00:21:32,260 --> 00:21:34,690
to your email list without
facing some issues.

508
00:21:34,690 --> 00:21:37,090
Not only is it against Etsy's policies,

509
00:21:37,090 --> 00:21:38,955
it's also illegal in many countries.

510
00:21:38,955 --> 00:21:40,990
Selling on Shopify also allows you

511
00:21:40,990 --> 00:21:43,510
to set yourself apart
from the competition.

512
00:21:43,510 --> 00:21:45,190
The bad thing about Etsy is

513
00:21:45,190 --> 00:21:47,140
that your products are always surrounded

514
00:21:47,140 --> 00:21:50,080
by your competitors, so
you are somewhat forced

515
00:21:50,080 --> 00:21:51,400
to compete on price.

516
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:53,530
It's kind of like this YouTube channel.

517
00:21:53,530 --> 00:21:54,910
You've probably got tons

518
00:21:54,910 --> 00:21:58,600
of other print on demand videos
recommended in the sidebar.

519
00:21:58,600 --> 00:22:00,880
I know I don't have to worry
about you clicking off my video

520
00:22:00,880 --> 00:22:02,710
though because it's the best one.

521
00:22:02,710 --> 00:22:05,530
Imagine this, you are
scrolling through YouTube,

522
00:22:05,530 --> 00:22:07,780
but all you are seeing are my videos.

523
00:22:07,780 --> 00:22:11,200
It's either stick with me or
don't learn anything at all.

524
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:13,840
It's kind of like having a Shopify store.

525
00:22:13,840 --> 00:22:16,780
If a customer wants what you
are selling, they can't go off

526
00:22:16,780 --> 00:22:18,280
and buy it from anyone else.

527
00:22:18,280 --> 00:22:20,410
You've got them right where you want them.

528
00:22:20,410 --> 00:22:24,340
So Shopify sounds like the
clear winner, right? Well, no.

529
00:22:24,340 --> 00:22:25,660
Here's what I suggest.

530
00:22:25,660 --> 00:22:27,820
When you're starting out
as a beginner, it's best

531
00:22:27,820 --> 00:22:29,230
to go with Etsy.

532
00:22:29,230 --> 00:22:32,020
The customer's already there,
which means you don't have

533
00:22:32,020 --> 00:22:33,610
to worry about marketing.

534
00:22:33,610 --> 00:22:36,040
All you have to focus on is getting better

535
00:22:36,040 --> 00:22:39,310
and better at designing
products people want to buy.

536
00:22:39,310 --> 00:22:41,980
The competition aspect
is actually very good

537
00:22:41,980 --> 00:22:45,430
for honing your skills as
the market doesn't lie.

538
00:22:45,430 --> 00:22:47,830
If your product designs
aren't good enough,

539
00:22:47,830 --> 00:22:49,510
then you won't make any sales.

540
00:22:49,510 --> 00:22:52,330
This will force you to find
unique gaps in the market

541
00:22:52,330 --> 00:22:54,280
and level up as an entrepreneur.

542
00:22:54,280 --> 00:22:57,160
You can also easily connect
it with gelato by going

543
00:22:57,160 --> 00:22:59,140
to a menu and stores.

544
00:22:59,140 --> 00:23:02,200
Don't get me wrong, the
end game should be Shopify.

545
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:05,170
However, before you start
spending crazy amounts

546
00:23:05,170 --> 00:23:08,410
of money on marketing for
products you don't even know sell,

547
00:23:08,410 --> 00:23:11,590
I recommend you post a
thousand listings on Etsy.

548
00:23:11,590 --> 00:23:14,650
This will set you back
about 20 cents per listing,

549
00:23:14,650 --> 00:23:17,140
which will be a total of $200,

550
00:23:17,140 --> 00:23:20,320
but the data you gather
will be worth far more.

551
00:23:20,320 --> 00:23:22,750
Once you've identified
your winning products,

552
00:23:22,750 --> 00:23:24,940
you can start building a Shopify store

553
00:23:24,940 --> 00:23:26,980
and advertising on TikTok.

554
00:23:26,980 --> 00:23:29,260
That way you'll know if your
products aren't selling on

555
00:23:29,260 --> 00:23:32,200
Shopify, then your marketing needs work.

556
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:34,600
If you just skip the Etsy step,

557
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:36,940
then the issue could also be your product

558
00:23:36,940 --> 00:23:39,430
and then it's hard to
tell what needs improving.

559
00:23:39,430 --> 00:23:43,660
Think of Etsy a bit like a
testing ground where you can cast

560
00:23:43,660 --> 00:23:46,610
as many fishing lines as
possible into the ocean,

561
00:23:46,610 --> 00:23:49,100
and when you start catching some big fish,

562
00:23:49,100 --> 00:23:51,200
you know it's time to take the next step.

563
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:53,720
So how do beginners sell on Etsy?

564
00:23:53,720 --> 00:23:56,420
Once you've created an
account, there are three hacks

565
00:23:56,420 --> 00:23:59,330
that you can do to help
you get notice on Etsy

566
00:23:59,330 --> 00:24:00,740
and make more sales.

567
00:24:00,740 --> 00:24:03,650
The first hack is to
make attractive mockups.

568
00:24:03,650 --> 00:24:05,780
This is super important
as people wanna see

569
00:24:05,780 --> 00:24:08,480
what your item looks
like in the real world,

570
00:24:08,480 --> 00:24:10,520
and mockups are an easy way for you

571
00:24:10,520 --> 00:24:12,080
to show them without having

572
00:24:12,080 --> 00:24:14,300
to order all the different
colors and designs

573
00:24:14,300 --> 00:24:15,590
and taking photos.

574
00:24:15,590 --> 00:24:16,610
Mockups also seem

575
00:24:16,610 --> 00:24:19,280
to make the product
look much more homemade,

576
00:24:19,280 --> 00:24:22,310
which instantly makes it seem
more valuable to customers.

577
00:24:22,310 --> 00:24:25,670
Gelatos built-in mock-up
studio actually makes this

578
00:24:25,670 --> 00:24:26,870
super simple.

579
00:24:26,870 --> 00:24:29,065
Now, this one here, there you go.

580
00:24:29,065 --> 00:24:31,940
That looks pretty good,
so let's go with that.

581
00:24:31,940 --> 00:24:35,270
The second hack is to
use the best keywords.

582
00:24:35,270 --> 00:24:39,440
This is extremely effective
as Etsy is a search engine,

583
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:41,750
so the more information you
can give them about your

584
00:24:41,750 --> 00:24:42,830
product, the better.

585
00:24:42,830 --> 00:24:45,110
Of course, you shouldn't use
keywords that don't apply

586
00:24:45,110 --> 00:24:48,110
to your product 'cause you
only want traffic from people

587
00:24:48,110 --> 00:24:51,020
that are interested in
pieing what you are selling.

588
00:24:51,020 --> 00:24:52,550
This is pretty simple to do.

589
00:24:52,550 --> 00:24:55,250
So let's go back to the listing we found

590
00:24:55,250 --> 00:24:57,680
to inspire our T-shirt design.

591
00:24:57,680 --> 00:25:01,760
As we can see, they've
used wood shirt, men

592
00:25:01,760 --> 00:25:06,295
woodworker shirt, men's
funny shirt, funny shirts

593
00:25:06,295 --> 00:25:09,500
for men and Father's Day
gift and dad's shirt.

594
00:25:09,500 --> 00:25:10,520
So I'll just copy

595
00:25:10,520 --> 00:25:13,460
and paste these keywords
into my tags and title.

596
00:25:13,460 --> 00:25:14,960
It's also worth looking around

597
00:25:14,960 --> 00:25:16,700
for different listings in case some

598
00:25:16,700 --> 00:25:19,730
of them have other unique
keywords you can copy.

599
00:25:19,730 --> 00:25:22,790
The third hack is to use premium branding.

600
00:25:22,790 --> 00:25:25,280
You need to convey quality and trust.

601
00:25:25,280 --> 00:25:28,550
Now, trust is the most
important thing in business

602
00:25:28,550 --> 00:25:29,605
and you're not gonna get there

603
00:25:29,605 --> 00:25:32,000
by looking like a shop
at the local market.

604
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:35,060
You need to go for that
premium boutique feel.

605
00:25:35,060 --> 00:25:38,030
This is a great example of a premium store

606
00:25:38,030 --> 00:25:39,620
with a clear identity.

607
00:25:39,620 --> 00:25:43,190
You can use the free Shopify
name generator to create a name

608
00:25:43,190 --> 00:25:46,310
that conveys trust and
is relevant to your shop.

609
00:25:46,310 --> 00:25:48,350
Then use the name checker website

610
00:25:48,350 --> 00:25:51,140
to see if it's available
across different platforms.

611
00:25:51,140 --> 00:25:53,960
The most crucial platform is Etsy,

612
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:57,320
but you should also check if
it's free on other social media

613
00:25:57,320 --> 00:26:00,080
platforms and for the
name, name availability.

614
00:26:00,080 --> 00:26:01,250
When creating your logo

615
00:26:01,250 --> 00:26:03,770
and banner, don't spend too
much time perfecting it.

616
00:26:03,770 --> 00:26:07,280
Instead, focus on making
it clean and professional.

617
00:26:07,280 --> 00:26:10,880
Canva offers numerous
templates that can be helpful.

618
00:26:10,880 --> 00:26:13,280
The key to a good Etsy banner is

619
00:26:13,280 --> 00:26:16,400
to make it reflect the
charm of homemade goods,

620
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:18,680
which corporate banners often lack.

621
00:26:18,680 --> 00:26:22,015
Lastly, make sure your shop
isn't targeting a completely

622
00:26:22,015 --> 00:26:23,270
different audience.

623
00:26:23,270 --> 00:26:25,850
I mean, you wouldn't expect
to walk into an Apple store

624
00:26:25,850 --> 00:26:30,110
and see a washing machine, even
though they could sell them.

625
00:26:30,110 --> 00:26:31,790
They understand the importance

626
00:26:31,790 --> 00:26:35,060
of maintaining a coherent brand image.

627
00:26:35,060 --> 00:26:37,010
If you wanna make sales quickly,

628
00:26:37,010 --> 00:26:40,430
then you are probably thinking,
when should I run paid ads?

629
00:26:40,430 --> 00:26:42,710
I understand the appeal
of running paid ads

630
00:26:42,710 --> 00:26:45,450
as they can instantly
give your sales a boost.

631
00:26:45,450 --> 00:26:49,050
However, in my opinion, people
start using paid ads well

632
00:26:49,050 --> 00:26:50,760
before they're actually ready.

633
00:26:50,760 --> 00:26:53,430
This means they either
end up with no sales

634
00:26:53,430 --> 00:26:56,940
or as soon as they turn
paid ads off their sales

635
00:26:56,940 --> 00:26:58,230
completely dry up.

636
00:26:58,230 --> 00:26:59,910
I've always built my businesses

637
00:26:59,910 --> 00:27:01,890
with an organic first approach.

638
00:27:01,890 --> 00:27:05,100
We are living in an age of more
free reach than ever before,

639
00:27:05,100 --> 00:27:08,855
and I actually think social
media companies are gonna start

640
00:27:08,855 --> 00:27:10,770
limiting organic reach soon

641
00:27:10,770 --> 00:27:12,690
as they must be losing out on millions

642
00:27:12,690 --> 00:27:14,010
of advertising dollars.

643
00:27:14,010 --> 00:27:15,185
The first thing you need

644
00:27:15,185 --> 00:27:17,795
to put your marketing
money into is creating

645
00:27:17,795 --> 00:27:19,530
short form content.

646
00:27:19,530 --> 00:27:23,490
This is great as you can post
it across Instagram, TikTok,

647
00:27:23,490 --> 00:27:24,810
YouTube shorts.

648
00:27:24,810 --> 00:27:27,690
It's the first type of
content that enables you

649
00:27:27,690 --> 00:27:29,970
to reach multiple different platforms

650
00:27:29,970 --> 00:27:32,430
and it's perfect for
showing off your products.

651
00:27:32,430 --> 00:27:34,260
You'd need to order a few samples,

652
00:27:34,260 --> 00:27:36,930
which I'd recommend
doing anyway as you need

653
00:27:36,930 --> 00:27:38,820
to double check the quality of the items

654
00:27:38,820 --> 00:27:39,930
that you are sending out.

655
00:27:39,930 --> 00:27:41,910
Then it's just a case
of creating some kind

656
00:27:41,910 --> 00:27:43,440
of story around your product.

657
00:27:43,440 --> 00:27:45,120
Don't just get fancy shots

658
00:27:45,120 --> 00:27:47,760
of someone wearing it or using it.

659
00:27:47,760 --> 00:27:50,010
Actually make it a part of a story.

660
00:27:50,010 --> 00:27:53,250
Remember, people are on social
media to be entertained,

661
00:27:53,250 --> 00:27:56,640
so if your content isn't
entertaining, then it won't reach

662
00:27:56,640 --> 00:27:57,720
as many people.

663
00:27:57,720 --> 00:28:00,750
The more views you get,
the more people will buy.

664
00:28:00,750 --> 00:28:01,950
It's as simple as that.

665
00:28:01,950 --> 00:28:04,920
The beauty of doing it this
way is that you are able to see

666
00:28:04,920 --> 00:28:08,220
what videos perform best
with your target audience

667
00:28:08,220 --> 00:28:11,280
before putting any ad spend
into boosting the views.

668
00:28:11,280 --> 00:28:13,830
Once you're seeing some
organic success, it's time

669
00:28:13,830 --> 00:28:16,560
to start supercharging
it with some paid ads.

670
00:28:16,560 --> 00:28:18,600
This way you are building
your side hustle on

671
00:28:18,600 --> 00:28:20,250
solid foundations.

672
00:28:20,250 --> 00:28:23,310
I've seen so many people lose
their Facebook ad accounts

673
00:28:23,310 --> 00:28:25,260
and it's just ruined their businesses.

674
00:28:25,260 --> 00:28:27,420
These platforms don't
have enough employees

675
00:28:27,420 --> 00:28:30,000
to oversee everything,
so they rely on tech

676
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:31,680
to police it for them.

677
00:28:31,680 --> 00:28:34,020
Don't leave your income
in the hands of ai,

678
00:28:34,020 --> 00:28:36,990
but that's not the biggest
thing people do wrong.

679
00:28:36,990 --> 00:28:39,540
So what's the most common mistake?

680
00:28:39,540 --> 00:28:42,330
A lot of people get drawn
in by the huge figures.

681
00:28:42,330 --> 00:28:45,480
Many people say they're
making with print on demand,

682
00:28:45,480 --> 00:28:48,930
but it's important to remember
anyone can sell at break even

683
00:28:48,930 --> 00:28:50,070
or even a loss.

684
00:28:50,070 --> 00:28:52,800
I have a feeling a lot of
these print on demand, Gus

685
00:28:52,800 --> 00:28:55,020
and drop shippers actually do this.

686
00:28:55,020 --> 00:28:56,970
They just make a loss on their products

687
00:28:56,970 --> 00:29:00,750
and then flex their revenue
figures on YouTube to young

688
00:29:00,750 --> 00:29:02,280
and impressionable people.

689
00:29:02,280 --> 00:29:03,515
Don't make the mistake

690
00:29:03,515 --> 00:29:06,450
of focusing on the revenue
you are generating.

691
00:29:06,450 --> 00:29:07,920
This is a profit gain

692
00:29:07,920 --> 00:29:09,300
and it's important to remember

693
00:29:09,300 --> 00:29:12,390
that your profit margins are everything

694
00:29:12,390 --> 00:29:15,090
and you should be protecting
them at all costs.

695
00:29:15,090 --> 00:29:17,460
I used to sell a lot of items on eBay.

696
00:29:17,460 --> 00:29:20,670
I remember having one competitor
in particular who'd always

697
00:29:20,670 --> 00:29:22,650
tried to undercut beyond price.

698
00:29:22,650 --> 00:29:25,620
Instead of competing, I'd
wait until he sold out.

699
00:29:25,620 --> 00:29:29,460
Then I'd continue to sell my
products at my normal price.

700
00:29:29,460 --> 00:29:31,080
The surprising thing is most

701
00:29:31,080 --> 00:29:34,530
of the time my competitor
only made 5% profit margin.

702
00:29:34,530 --> 00:29:36,240
Whenever I saw him at trade shows,

703
00:29:36,240 --> 00:29:39,390
he would laugh thinking he'd
driven me out of the market.

704
00:29:39,390 --> 00:29:43,540
I just smile to myself as still
have my 30% profit margins

705
00:29:43,540 --> 00:29:45,400
and I was making bang.

706
00:29:45,400 --> 00:29:47,620
The same applies with any business.

707
00:29:47,620 --> 00:29:49,420
Don't let your ego get in the way.

708
00:29:49,420 --> 00:29:52,210
You don't have to be ranked
number one to make money.

709
00:29:52,210 --> 00:29:54,730
As long as your profit margins are strong,

710
00:29:54,730 --> 00:29:57,370
you could be making more
money than the top sellers.

711
00:29:57,370 --> 00:29:59,050
If you are choosing the Etsy route,

712
00:29:59,050 --> 00:30:03,070
this is even more crucial
due to the associated fees.

713
00:30:03,070 --> 00:30:08,070
Etsy charges 6.5% transaction
fee on both the price

714
00:30:08,140 --> 00:30:11,080
and the shipping fee when
the item sells, as well

715
00:30:11,080 --> 00:30:14,805
as a 3% payment processing
fee on the total amount

716
00:30:14,805 --> 00:30:16,090
charged to the customer.

717
00:30:16,090 --> 00:30:19,360
Here's a little secret that
not a lot of people know about.

718
00:30:19,360 --> 00:30:20,440
You might be hit

719
00:30:20,440 --> 00:30:24,820
with a 15% advertising fee if
a customer stumbles upon your

720
00:30:24,820 --> 00:30:28,090
product through an Etsy ad
from outside the platform.

721
00:30:28,090 --> 00:30:29,980
Sure, you can opt out,

722
00:30:29,980 --> 00:30:33,610
but honestly, it's not a bad
deal as long as you're clued in

723
00:30:33,610 --> 00:30:35,290
and factor it into your cost

724
00:30:35,290 --> 00:30:37,780
and hey, don't forget about your time.

725
00:30:37,780 --> 00:30:40,180
It isn't free. You know it's a shame,

726
00:30:40,180 --> 00:30:43,690
but loads of people seem to
forget to value their own time.

727
00:30:43,690 --> 00:30:45,490
I mean, if they were to do the math

728
00:30:45,490 --> 00:30:48,670
and figure out their hourly
earnings, they might be shocked

729
00:30:48,670 --> 00:30:51,460
to find out they're making
less than minimum wage.

730
00:30:51,460 --> 00:30:53,260
Now at the start, you're
probably gonna have

731
00:30:53,260 --> 00:30:56,080
to hustle a bit more and
earn a little bit less.

732
00:30:56,080 --> 00:30:57,340
That's understandable,

733
00:30:57,340 --> 00:30:59,440
but just keep a close eye
on the profits you are

734
00:30:59,440 --> 00:31:01,030
making every so often.

735
00:31:01,030 --> 00:31:04,120
Divide your monthly profit
by the hours you've put in.

736
00:31:04,120 --> 00:31:06,160
This will give you a pretty good picture

737
00:31:06,160 --> 00:31:08,650
of whether your side hustle
is on the right track or not.

738
00:31:08,650 --> 00:31:11,020
But now it's time for the big question.

739
00:31:11,020 --> 00:31:13,780
Can I really make money
with print on demand

740
00:31:13,780 --> 00:31:15,610
or is it too saturated?

741
00:31:15,610 --> 00:31:18,880
Right? So I need to address
a negative comment I received

742
00:31:18,880 --> 00:31:21,460
about this on my last
print on demand video.

743
00:31:21,460 --> 00:31:24,340
Mark, be honest about the
content of your vlogs.

744
00:31:24,340 --> 00:31:26,680
Tell people how saturated the markets are

745
00:31:26,680 --> 00:31:28,960
and stop giving them four solutions.

746
00:31:28,960 --> 00:31:31,090
The world of side hustles are over.

747
00:31:31,090 --> 00:31:33,190
There's no such thing as a quick buck.

748
00:31:33,190 --> 00:31:34,990
First of all, I wanna say thanks

749
00:31:34,990 --> 00:31:36,640
for taking the time to comment.

750
00:31:36,640 --> 00:31:39,370
I really appreciate when
you guys leave comments.

751
00:31:39,370 --> 00:31:40,930
I love reading your opinions

752
00:31:40,930 --> 00:31:43,570
and love to hear about
all your success as well.

753
00:31:43,570 --> 00:31:45,970
Although there are a couple
of things I disagree with,

754
00:31:45,970 --> 00:31:48,250
which we'll get into a bit later.

